  "blurb": "An award-winning hillside villa above Coral Cove on Koh Samui's east coast, wrapped in 180-degree sea views with four en-suite bedrooms, five bathrooms and a terraced pool set into landscaped gardens — with full-time staff, daily continental breakfast and lunch, an in-house Muay Thai instructor and airport transfers, sleeping up to eight across 350 m².",
  "detail": "Set high on the hillside above prestigious Coral Cove on Koh Samui's east coast, this villa was built to make the most of one thing above all — the view, which sweeps a full 180 degrees over the cove and the sea beyond. Its architecture has been recognised repeatedly, including Best Villa Architecture & Design at the Thailand Property Awards, and the 350 m² of space is arranged so the outlook follows you from room to room.\n\nFour en-suite bedrooms and five bathrooms sleep up to eight, with living and dining spaces that open onto a terraced pool set into landscaped, fully private gardens. The design keeps the villa secluded while framing the water, and the terracing steps the pool and lounging areas down toward the horizon.\n\nA full-time team looks after the stay with daily housekeeping, complimentary continental breakfast and lunch, and dinner available on request, alongside unlimited utilities, WiFi and airport transfers. There is even an in-house Muay Thai instructor for guests who want to train with a view. Chaweng's beach, restaurants and nightlife are a short drive down the hill, with the quieter sands of Coral Cove closer still.",
